THE Limpopo Department of Economic Development, Environment
and Tourism (LEDET) says six lions are on the loose between Giyani and
Malamulele, after they were seen in the area. The department says they have sent a team of rangers to the
area. LEDET spokesperson Burckels Napo said there’s a person who
called the offices on Saturday night and alerted them, that six lions around
the R81 between Giyani and Malamulele. Napo said they are busy looking for the lions, but they haven’t
been able to locate them, however they are still on the site. “I hope they might have returned to the park, because during
the night they can travel almost between 20 to 30 kilometres per night,” said
Napo. He also said he will give a full report to the team.